{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, GAI also outperforms traditional AI techniques in data analysis and feature extraction, showing great potential in enabling wireless communication.",
    "For example, Balevi et al. [251] proposed a GANs-based channel estimation scheme for wideband channels with low SINR, achieving superior performance over the traditional ResNet model.",
    "Specifically, they first used GANs to generate the channel samples from the real but unknown channel distribution in the offline training phase.",
    "In the online testing stage, the trained GANs were used as a prior for channel estimation according to the received signal.",
    "Therefore, there is a trend to use GAI to support ISAC systems from different perspectives."
  ]
}